// Example extraction logic in Dart (simplified)
String extractMermaidCode(String modelOutput) {
  final startTag = '<DIAGRAM>';
  final endTag = '</DIAGRAM>';
  final startIndex = modelOutput.indexOf(startTag);
  final endIndex = modelOutput.indexOf(endTag);

  if (startIndex != -1 && endIndex != -1 && endIndex > startIndex) {
    return modelOutput
        .substring(startIndex + startTag.length, endIndex)
        .trim();
  }
  return ''; // Fallback or error handling
}

This approach leverages the system prompt's XML-style delimiters to reliably isolate Mermaid code, even if the model includes additional explanatory text outside the tags.
